## 4. Concepts locked in at this milestone

- CI as automated QA; gates re-examine every push, no permanent passes
- Three machines: laptop / runner / image; dev vs prod dependencies
- Jobs parallel by default; `needs:` chains them; steps sequential within a job
- Linters vs formatters; house rules vs universal law; hard gates with tuned rules
- Mocking (fakeredis, monkeypatched time); unit vs integration; two nets, different holes
- `if __name__ == "__main__"`; importable-without-side-effects
- Coverage as a flashlight, not a grade; artifacts as evidence
- Registries; SHA-vs-latest tagging; service containers in CI
- CVEs; severity gating; ignore-unfixed policy; base-image rot and build-time patching
- Poll-with-deadline; `if: failure()` / `if: always()`; log dumps as postmortem evidence
- Failure-layer diagnosis before fixing

## 5. Next (Milestone 04)
Deploy: provision the minimum viable target (single EC2, Docker + compose), GitHub Secrets for SSH credentials, and a rolling-update script — start new, wait for health, cut over only if healthy, abort within 60 seconds otherwise. The "make things visible only when fully ready" principle from the Stage 2 race condition, at deployment scale.
